<br>
A story written roughly 3 months ago, on a Message board unaffiliated with Sony or Verant Interactive (VI), was anonymously forwarded to VI.  The VI staff found this not to their liking and banned the player who wrote it.  Admittedly, the post is graphic and controversial.  But it was well written and in character.<br>
<br>
This has caused a huge outrage within the Brell community and at large.  <br>
<br>
Beyond the banning off Mystere, it has raised a whole series of other role playing issues:  <br>
<br>
What are the acceptable guide lines?<br>
How CAN an evil race be played?<br>
Should RP writing, out of game, be a ban-able offence?<br>
Who is next?<br>
<br>
The biggest question on all of our lips is this: How does activity on a non-VI or Sony Message board warrant banning?<br>
<br>
Abashi has responded thusly:<br>
<br>
Like all other account issues, this is a matter between us and the owner of the<br>
account. It's not something that we're going to discuss or justify publicly. <br>
<br>
We make determinations based on information at hand regarding who is or is not having a positive affect on EverQuest's community. If we determine that one person's actions make EverQuest a game that other people do not want to play based upon those actions, we will exercise our right to refuse service to the extent necessary to provide a reasonable and enjoyable gaming environment.<br>
<br>
This is the extent to which we'll address this specific issue. If people have general questions not related to the specific issues in this case, I'll be happy to field them tomorrow. This issue is however closed.<br>
